						               													<description>A.T.R.: Ahora Todos Re&amp;iacute;mos is a lighter version of H.D.P.: Hasta Donde Puedas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play begins with a judge a.k.a. A.T.R. playing a black card with a question or fill-in-the-blank phrase from the top of the deck and showing it to all players. Each player holds a hand of ten white answer cards at the beginning of each round, and passes a card to the A.T.R., face-down, representing their answer to the question on the card. The A.T.R. determines which answer card is the funniest one in the context of the question or fill-in-the-blank card. The player who submitted the chosen card is given the question card to represent a point, and then the player to the left of the A.T.R. becomes the new A.T.R. for the next round. Play continues until a player collects 5 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
